CMPUT 275 Winter 2022

Weekly Exercise #7: Mountain Climbing

Included Files:
	climbing.cpp
	README
	Makefile

Running Instructions: 
	In the directory containing included files highlighted above, either run the command "g++ -o <name_of_choice> climbing.cpp" to compile and link the cpp file to make an executable or run "make" (which will compile and link to a executable named we7_solution).
	Afterwards, run "./<name_of_choice>" to execute the executable. 

Notes and Assumptions: 
	The input will contain two lines: the first contains three space-separated positive integers - length, rest, and limit. The second containes length spaced-separated postiive integers, representing the heights of ledges in array heights. It is assumed that that the second line will be typed in ascending order.

	All input values must be unsigned integers.
